\cf8 Very Good Tip:  If you use layers well, you can divide you level into different layers and get Pfhorge drawing faster.    Layers with anything from 0 to 400 polygons work well.  Pfhorge supports unlimited amount of polygons in each layer.  Pfhorge will not have to draw other polygons in other layers speeding up drawing.\
\
With layers you could have a 10,000 polygon map and still have good drawing speed.\
\
Another good tip is to connect polygons between layers in the "No Layer On" layer.  You should divide up you level is such a way that you should not have to do very much "Layer Connecting" or "Layer Joining", where you connect polygons between layers.\cf9 \
