You setup how layers will be automatically created at level loading time via "File->Pfhorge Prefs->Default Layers." When you click on that menu item, a window will open.  You use the sliders/text boxes at the bottom to adjust the range.  Any polys at load time that are within the range (Both there Ceiling and Floor Height have to be within the corasponding ranges) will be assigned to that layer.  Also, when the program is determining which layer the poly should be long to at level load time, it will start at the top of the list and work its way down. When it finds a layer that the poly is in range of, it will assign that poly to that layer and then go on to the next poly, stopping its search at that point.  So layers will override any layer underneath it.  that last layer will always be the "Default Layer" with a floor range from -9wu to 9wu, and a ceiling range from -9wu to 9wu. So it will basically collect any polygons that do not get assigned to any layers above it. Right now weird things 
