1. You can now name tags, lights, liquids (media), platforms, ambient sounds, and random sounds. To open the name editor for a document, make sure the the document you want to edit is the front most (the active document). Open the Tools menu, then select the first menu item , named "Edit Tag Names, Etc."   The new names should show up in the inspector and anywhere else relevant in the program. Please keep in mind that each document keeps track of its names, and that each document can have a separate window for each document for editing the names.  If you have more then one document open, you could also have more then one naming window open also (one for each document, if you wanted to), make sure you do not mix them up and start naming things for one level meant for another.  I will fix it so that it will be obvious which document the name editor will edit in the future. For right now, simply close the name editor after you are done to avoid confusion if you have more then one document open at the same time.\
